**Q4: How do you implement an auth-protected route?**

**A:** In go_router, use the top-level `redirect:` callback. It fires before every navigation and can return a new path to redirect to, or `null` to allow:
```dart
redirect: (context, state) {
  final loggedIn = auth.isLoggedIn;
  final atLogin = state.matchedLocation == '/login';
  if (!loggedIn && !atLogin) return '/login';
  if (loggedIn && atLogin) return '/';
  return null;
}
```
One source of truth. Avoid ad-hoc auth checks in each screen ŌĆö they cause flicker (screen briefly renders before redirect fires) and duplicated logic. Combine with a `refreshListenable` (a `ValueListenable<AuthState>`) so the router re-evaluates guards when the user logs in/out.
